"n.范例，示范 【英】 n. 范例，示范(a typical example or archetype) 【记】 para(旁边)＋digm(显 示)→显示给旁边的看 →榜样 【同】 派生词: paradigmatic (adj. 作为示范的 ，典范的 ) n. 范例, 示范 【记】para旁边, dig挖, m－在旁边挖井给大家水喝－榜样 【参】paradigmatic(adj 作为示范的, 典范的) 【类】paragon[paradigm]: imitate = reverence: regard模范值得效仿 = 尊敬的人值得尊重corrective: amends = paradigm[paragon]: exemplify补救物用来补偿 = 范例用来例证 【记】源自pare- 旁，compare + diagram 图，用来比较的图画→范例；parade 游行，检阅，展示，游行与阅兵展示的都是典型与范例 paradigm (n.)  late 15c., from Late Latin paradigma ""pattern, example,"" especially in grammar, from Greek paradeigma ""pattern, model; precedent, example,"" from paradeiknynai ""exhibit, represent,"" literally ""show side by side,"" from para- ""beside"" (see para- (1)) + deiknynai ""to show"" (cognate with Latin dicere ""to show;"" see diction). Related: Paradigmatic; paradigmatical."
